  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increase Milk production for Sustainable Business</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Chepkorio dairies average production in 2019 was 8 000ltrs and target for 2020 is 15 000ltrs per day. To achieve this  the focus will beon building the capacity of the staff in extension and quality department to ensure good quality and increased production  hence the sustainable services review workshop. Chepkorio intends to reduce the sale of raw milk revenues from Kshs 56 Million in 2020 to Kshs 17Million by year 2021; therefore they will start venturing into high value milk products with a target to process the entire milk daily collection  hence the need for a good marketing strategy that will guide them in establishing and penetrating new markets. To succesfully venture in high value products  investments are needed therefore need to build own capital by mobilising shareholders or through increased sale of milk. An internal caital training is therefore important to help define the priorities.&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Increase milk production from 8 000ltrs per day to 15 000ltrs per day&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Mobilise shares through &amp;nbsp;1 000 shareholders with min of ksh. 2 000 and max of sh.6 000&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Reduce the sale of raw milk revenues from Kshs 56 Million &amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&lt;p&gt;Share capital mobilisation and Internal capital workshop&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Market strategy development&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;review sustatinable services plan&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Train quality and extension staff for increased quality of milk&lt;/p&gt;</narrative>
  </description>
